					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016#post-4136223</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016/scp-3431#post-4136223</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 31 Jan 2019 00:52:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's intentionally &quot;irregularities&quot;, since referring to deviations from the norm that <em>aren't</em> anomalous. Basically just unusual or weird qualities that could happen IRL.</p> <p>&quot;Anomalies&quot; used in this context would refer to the can't-be-explained-by-science deviations/things the Foundation would need to contain.</p> <p>I'm glad you liked the article; thank you for the +1!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016#post-4136215</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016/scp-3431#post-4136215</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 31 Jan 2019 00:42:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheBlueHour</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4078000</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Okay, I know this is a minor nitpick, but shouldn't this:</p> <blockquote> <p>Samples taken from the trees indicated an unusually high chlorophyll concentration, but otherwise no irregularities.</p> </blockquote> <p>be:</p> <blockquote> <p>Samples taken from the trees indicated an unusually high chlorophyll concentration, but otherwise no anomalies.</p> </blockquote> <p>Or am off base here? Either way I enjoyed this, +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016#post-4136126</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016/scp-3431#post-4136126</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 30 Jan 2019 23:26:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm glad you like this! &quot;Strange and there&quot; is definitely the feel I was going for with this; I feel like it's pretty indicative of the average Foundation investigation process. Doesn't make for the most adrenaline-rushing exciting job, but you never know what the next anomaly will be kinda thing. And also I like the mental image of a pair of Foundation agents having to repeatedly go into a koala enclosure to retrieve their watches and phones, just to see if that happens every time they observe the anomaly.</p> <p>Thanks for the upvote!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
