					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016#post-3858063</guid>
				<title>Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6277016/scp-3431#post-3858063</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 02 Jul 2018 01:21:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Big thanks to everyone who read over this in chat!</p> <ul> <li>Modern_Erasmus</li> <li>sepjkl (refused koala)</li> <li>Prototype_Toaster</li> <li>mlister</li> <li>Clout</li> <li>subtletea</li> <li>not_a_seagull</li> <li>Rimple</li> <li>ResearcherBlasko</li> <li>salvagebar (accepted koala)</li> </ul> <p>So, this is another weird idea of mine that came partially from a chat conversation. The discussion started by people finding synonyms for the phrase &quot;trash panda&quot;:</p> <blockquote> <p>famine garbage bear.<br /> famine refuse koala<br /> Zyn &gt; 14:32 famine refuse koala<br /> Zyn I envisioned a sign that has like<br /> Zyn a shady-looking koala offering candy to a kid<br /> Zyn and the kid is holding up their hand like &quot;no&quot;<br /> Zyn and the sign is captioned &quot;Refuse Koala&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>And then I wanted to write this into a short Series-I-esque article. And here we are. Did you know that koalas are pretty weird and sometimes terrible animals? Although that said, I think they're cute from a distance&#8230;</p> <p>Refuse koala.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
